      "content": "A warm compress can help bring the discharge to a head, but you should be careful not to overdo it. Soaking the area in warm water for 5-10 minutes a few times a day might help loosen the discharge, and Neosporin is a good choice to help prevent infection. Just remember to pat the area dry with a clean towel after washing and apply a thin layer of ointment, rather than applying too much pressure, which could push the discharge further into the skin.",
